description: Tick Reports map shows locations and counts of public-reported ticks in DuPage Co for the 2018 season. Depending on the species, ticks can transmit Lyme disease, Rocky Mountain spotted fever or other illness to humans.? ?DuPage County Health Department uses a suite of maps - Tick Reports, Bird Deaths, and Mosquito pools infected with West Nile virus to track the potential for human illness to increase due to mosquitoes and tics.? These maps will be updated weekly throughout the season to promote public awareness and education.

title: ParcelsRealEstate
description:
Notice:?

1. If you download
this feature layer on our Open data website.
The process may be slow. This feature layer is very large.?

2. Several field names
are truncated or altered when you download the data. The field names (within
the download) will not match the attribute field names listed below in this
description.

?

This feature layer
contains the most current parcels data with real estate data for DuPage County,
Illinois. The dataset was created and is maintained by the DuPage County
Information Technology Department, GIS Division in conjunction with the DuPage
County Clerk for the visual and spatial representation of deeds, road
rights-of-way, and subdivision plats. The?ParcelsRealEstate?feature
layer contains the?Current?Assessment Parcels?as well as
the?Current?Real Estate File?which is joined to the
parcels on a weekly basis.
